            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I don't see any bugs `aucmd_defer()` can avoid, considering this is called just before returning from `do_put()` and executed with `textlock` set. On the other hand I can see using `aucmd_defer()` will cause bugs if one has a mapping with another operation immediately following a put.",
            "commit_id": "986382069a14f122522865934400ed1e9c41d418",
            "created_at": "2026-05-13T00:33:50Z",
